<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4505151>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figs 18–25. Last instar larva and pupa of Daiphron bipartitus Pic, 1934. 18–19 – right antenna (18 – dorsal view, 19 – ventral view). 20–21 – apex of right antenna (20 – ventral view, 21 – dorsal view); 22 – right prothoracic leg; 23 – pretarsus of prothoracic leg; 24 – mesothoracic spiracle; 25 – pupal abdominal tergite IX and urogomphi. Scale bars: 18–19 – 0.25 mm; 20, 21, 23, 24 – 0.05 mm; 22, 25 – 1.0 mm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4505151/files/figure.png" .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4505147>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figs 8–17. Last instar larva of Daiphron bipartitus Pic, 1934. 8–10 – head capsule, antennae and mouthparts removed (dorsal, frontal, fronto-lateral); 11–14 – right mandible (dorsal, mesal, ventral, lateral view); 15 – maxillo-labial complex; 16 – hypopharynx; 17 – galea. Scale bars: 8–10, 15, 16 – 0.5 mm; 11–14 – 0.2 mm; 17 – 0.05 mm. Abbrevations: mg – median groove; mi – median incision; np – nasal plate; nt – nasal teeth; pl – paranasal lobe." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4505147/files/figure.png" .

